er%20from%20the%20local%20utility%20grid.%20But%20they%20have%20to%20run%2024%2F7%2C%20so%20if%20that%20power%20goes%20out%2C%20they%20rely%20on%20backup%20generators%20that%20burn%20diesel%20fuel%20or%20natural%20gas.%20To%20run%20them%2C%20data%20center%20owners%20must%20get%20permits%2C%20which%20require%20an%20accurate%20accounting%20of%20their%20emissions.%20That%20output%20maps%20to%20the%20data%20center's%20power%20needs.%20By%20obtaining%201%2C240%20permits%20from%20across%20the%20US%2C%20Business%20Insider%20calculated%20the%20potential%20near-term%20ecological%20footprint%20of%20every%20US%20data%20center%20owner%2C%20based%20on%20our%20estimate%20of%20how%20much%20electricity%20data%20centers%20typically%20use%20relative%20to%20the%20capacity%20of%20their%20backup%20systems.%20(See%20here%20for%20more%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-calculate-data-center-cost-environmental-impact-methodology-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20methodology%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20tops%20the%20list.%20Business%20Insider's%20estimate%20indicates%20that%20if%20it%20builds%20all%20the%20data%20centers%20it%20has%20planned%2C%20it%20would%20use%2030%20to%2048%20terawatt-hours%20a%20year.%20At%20the%20midpoint%2C%20that%20would%20be%20around%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20electricity%20the%20state%20of%20Nevada%20used%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20said%20Business%20Insider's%20methodology%20for%20estimating%20consumption%20%26quot%3Boversimplifies%20complex%20data%20center%20operations%20and%20is%20based%20on%20assumptions%20that%20do%20not%20account%20for%20important%20differences%20in%20how%20companies%20build%20and%20operate%20data%20centers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20and%20Meta%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20queries%20about%20data%20center%20power%20use%20estimates%2C%20and%20QTS%20declined%20to%20comment.%20A%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%20acknowledged%20that%20its%20data%20centers%20%26quot%3Bdo%20not%20always%20run%20at%20100%25%20of%20their%20installed%20capacity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftbimedia.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2Fbistudios%2F_00%2Fdev_edit%2Fgraphics%2F2025%2F04%2F2025-04-data-centers-summaries%2Findex.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20data-chart%3D%5C%22summary-top10largest%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20government%20estimates%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Fai-energy-demand-power-data-centers-crypto-electric-grid-issues-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edemand%20for%20electricity%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20rise%20more%20this%20decade%20than%20it%20has%20since%20the%201980s%3B%20some%20calculations%20say%20data%20centers%20account%20for%20as%20much%20as%2044%25%20of%20that%20growth.%20Meeting%20that%20new%20demand%20will%20mean%20keeping%20older%2C%20dirtier%20generation%20capacity%20online%20%E2%80%94%20climate%20crisis%20and%20carbon%20commitments%20be%20damned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWater%20is%20the%20most%20effective%20way%20to%20cool%20down%20the%20hotter%2C%20more%20closely%20packed%20graphics%20processing%20units%20that%20AI%20relies%20on.%20And%20that%20water%20often%20has%20to%20be%20fresh.%20Data%20centers%20are%20finicky%20drinkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20before%20the%20AI%20boom%2C%20US%20data%20centers%20consumed%2034%20billion%20gallons%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20just%20about%20what%20the%20state%20of%20California%20uses%20every%20day.%20Just%20seven%20years%20later%2C%20the%20US%20has%20doubled%20its%20data%20center%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20here%20is%20where%20you'd%20expect%20a%20story%20like%20this%20to%20tell%20you%20how%20much%20water%20any%20data%20center%20of%20a%20given%20size%20uses.%20That's%20almost%20impossible.%20Just%20half%20of%20all%20data%20center%20operators%20track%20their%20water%20use%2C%20and%20it's%20wildly%20variable%20depending%20on%20size%20and%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223846%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Power%20lines%20in%20front%20of%20a%20coal-fired%20power%20station%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682503cc3fe8d3928365e17a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222885%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20natural%20gas%20plant%20run%20by%20Dominion%20Energy%20in%20Virginia.%20Data%20centers%20need%20vast%20amounts%20of%20electricity.%3Cp%3EGreg%20Kahn%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20the%20air%20permits%20Business%20Insider%20examined%2C%20we%20can%20at%20least%20tell%20you%20where%20those%20data%20centers%20are.%20That's%20important%20because%2C%20given%20their%20needs%2C%20you%20might%20think%20that%20companies%20would%20site%20them%20near%20ready%20supplies%20of%20fresh%20water.%20They%20often%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%2040%25%20of%20the%20data%20centers%20in%20the%20US%20are%20(or%20are%20set%20to%20be)%20in%20places%20marked%20by%20the%20World%20Resources%20Institute%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sustainability%20advocacy%20group%20%E2%80%94%20as%20having%20high%20or%20extremely%20high%20water%20scarcity.%20That%20includes%20multiple%20parts%20of%20the%20arid%20American%20Southwest%20%E2%80%94%20like%20Arizona's%20Maricopa%20County%2C%20an%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20water-stressed%20area%26quot%3B%20with%2048%20data%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20center%20builders%20know%20all%20this%2C%20and%20they%20take%20water%20seriously.%20The%20biggest%20water%20users%20have%20pledged%20to%20do%20better%20%E2%80%94%20to%20be%20water-neutral%20in%20coming%20years%2C%20to%20pay%20other%20users%20to%20use%20less%2C%20or%20to%20fund%20water%20conservation%20projects%20as%20offsets.%20And%20they%20point%20out%20that%20just%20because%20they%20have%20permission%20to%20use%20millions%20of%20g