truction%20in%20Chandler%2C%20Arizona.%3Cp%3EJesse%20Rieser%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20companies%20are%20spending%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20building%20data%20centers%2C%20racing%20to%20power%20an%20AI%20revolution%20they%20say%20will%20bring%20broad%20benefits%20and%20enormous%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20actual%20price%2C%20though%2C%20has%20never%20been%20fully%20measured.%20So%20a%20team%20of%20Business%20Insider%20reporters%20and%20editors%20set%20out%20to%20find%20the%20true%20cost%20of%20the%20US%20data%20center%20boom%20%E2%80%94%20in%20water%2C%20power%2C%20pollution%2C%20and%20tax%20incentives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20pulled%20obscure%20state%20records%2C%20scoured%20corporate%20disclosures%2C%20and%20sought%20analysis%20and%20guidance%20from%20government%20researchers%20in%20Virginia%20and%20elsewhere.%20We%20spoke%20to%20engineering%20specialists%20who%20study%20data%20centers%2C%20including%20Shaolei%20Ren%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Riverside%2C%20and%20Vijay%20Gadepally%20of%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology.%20We%20also%20spoke%20to%20researchers%20who%20study%20incentive%20packages%2C%20such%20as%20Kasia%20Tarczynska%20of%20Good%20Jobs%20First%2C%20a%20research%20group%20that%20advocates%20for%20transparency%20and%20equality%20in%20public%20subsidies.%20And%20we%20sought%20input%20from%20companies%20and%20industry%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20is%20the%20most%20complete%20accounting%20yet%20of%20data%20centers'%20impact%20on%20our%20environment%2C%20economy%2C%20and%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20we%20did%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a83f3d1-6c8d-450c-92ee-5757a8ac53e3%5C%22%3EWe%20started%20by%20identifying%20how%20many%20data%20centers%20there%20are%2C%20and%20who%20owns%20them%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EData%20centers%20can%20never%20be%20without%20power.%20Developers%20build%20backup%20generators%20to%20provide%20emergency%20electricity.%20Since%20these%20generators%20emit%20air%20pollution%2C%20they%20are%20regulated%20by%20state%20environmental%20agencies%20and%20need%20permits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20requested%20these%20air%20permits%20and%20applications%20from%2050%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20asking%20agencies%20to%20search%20permits%20using%20federal%20industry%20codes%20associated%20with%20data%20centers.%20To%20confirm%20state%20searches%20were%20complete%2C%20Business%20Insider%20cross-referenced%20permits%20against%20company%20disclosures%2C%20news%20articles%2C%20and%20data%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdatacentermap.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edatacentermap.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbaxtel.com%2Fmap%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBaxtel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20other%20trade%20websites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20permits%20we%20obtained%20were%20actually%20for%20other%20types%20of%20facilities.%20If%20public%20or%20corporate%20records%20confirmed%20the%20facility%20was%20not%20a%20data%20center%2C%20we%20removed%20it%20from%20our%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20compiled%20permits%20for%201%2C240%20existing%20or%20planned%20data%20centers%20across%20the%20country%2C%20the%20most%20definitive%20tally%20to%20date.%20Tracking%20the%20year%20each%20permit%20was%20first%20issued%20reveals%20a%20construction%20boom.%20Until%202010%2C%20companies%20had%20filed%20permits%20for%20311%20data%20centers.%20By%202024%2C%20that%20number%20had%20nearly%20quadrupled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOften%20the%20permit%20holders%20are%20subsidiaries%20of%20Big%20Tech%20companies%2C%20with%20unfamiliar%20names%20like%20Nova%20Mango%20Farms.%20Business%20Insider%20determined%20the%20owners%20using%20emails%2C%20addresses%2C%20and%20other%20information%20on%20permit%20applications%2C%20secretary-of-state%20disclosures%2C%20county%20databases%2C%20and%20SEC%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d8810ed-a100-46b1-a4b7-0ad80d6f3952%5C%22%3EThen%20we%20mapped%20those%20centers'%20locations%20and%20estimated%20the%20resources%20they%20consume%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20mapped%20location%20information%20from%20the%20permits%20onto%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wri.org%2Fapplications%2Faqueduct%2Fwater-risk-atlas%2F%23%2F%3Fadvanced%3Dfalse%26basemap%3Dhydro%26indicator%3Dw_awr_def_tot_cat%26lat%3D-14.445396942837744%26lng%3D-142.85354599620152%26mapMode%3Dview%26month%3D1%26opacity%3D0.5%26ponderation%3DDEF%26predefined%3Dfalse%26projection%3Dabsolute%26scenario%3Doptimistic%26scope%3Dbaseline%26timeScale%3Dannual%26year%3Dbaseline%26zoom%3D2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAqueduct%20Water%20Risk%20Atlas%3C%2Fa%3E%20built%20by%20the%20World%20Resources%20Institute%2C%20a%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20group%20that%20advocates%20sustainability.%20The%20atlas%20measures%20a%20location's%20relative%20water%20stress%20%E2%80%94%20the%20ratio%20between%20demand%20and%20available%2C%20renewable%20supplies.%20Business%20Insider%20found%20that%2040%25%20of%20data%20centers%20were%20sited%20in%20areas%20of%20high%20or%20extremely%20high%20water%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20centers%20can%20use%20staggering%20amounts%20of%20water.%20Business%20Insider%20requested%20metered%20water%20use%20records%20and%20water%20supply%20agreements%20from%20dozens%20of%20public%20utility%20agencies%20for%20every%20data%20center%20in%20areas%20with%20extremely%20high%20water%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20center%20water%20use%20is%20a%20closely%20guarded%20secret.%20Many%20agencies%20denied%20our%20requests%20for%20facility-specific%20water%20use%20or%20released%20the%20records%20only%20in%20aggregate%20for%20all%20data%20centers%20in%20a%20water%20utility's%20service%20area.%20In%20Denver%20and%20Colorado%20Springs%2C%20Colorado%2C%20utility%20agencies%20sued%20Business%20Insider%20to%20prevent%20the%20release%20of%20metered%20water%20use%20records.%20Business%20Insider%20prevailed%20in%20both%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20found%20that%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20data%20center%20facilities%20were%20permitted%20to%20use%20more%20water%20a%20day%20than%20you%20might%20expect%20nearly%2049%2C000%20Americans%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20also%20disclose%20little%20information%20on%20how%20much%20power%20their%20US%20data%20centers%20consume.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-centers-us-power-grid-gpu-nvidia-cerebras-amazon-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EData%20center%20power%20use%3C%2Fa%3E%20varies%20based%20on%20factors%20including%20the%20types%20and%20frequency%20of%20use%20of%20servers%2C%20cooling%20systems%2C%20and%20other%20infrastructure.%20To%20account%20for%20this%2C%20Business%20Insider%20calculated%20a%20range%20of%20estimated%20annual%20data%20center%20electricity%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20calculate%20this%20range%2C%20Business%20Insider%20used%20air%20permit%20data%20to%20identify%20the%20total%20power-generation%20capacity%20of%20every%20backup%20generator%20at%20each%20facility.%20Companies%20rarely%20install%20generator%20capacity%20that%20is%20more%20than%20twice%20what%20a%20data%20center%20consumes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20often%20they%20install%20significantly%20less%20than%20that.%20So%20Business%20Insider%2C%20in%20consultation%20with%20experts%2C%20conservatively%20estimated%20that%20a%20data%20center's%20maximum%20electricity%20use%20is%20between%20half%20and%2080%25%20of%20its%20generators'%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feta-publications.lbl.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-12%2Flbnl-2024-united-states-data-center-energy-usage-report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20federal%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimates%20that%20across%20the%20industry%2C%20data%20centers%20operate%20at%20just%2050%25%20of%20that%20maximum%20electricity%20use%20level%2C%20to%20avoid%20straining%20their%20equipment.%20So%20Business%20Insider%20multiplied%20the%20low%20and%20high%20ends%20of%20its%20initial%20range%20by%2050%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20data%20includes%20permits%20for%20data%20centers%20that%20are%20not%20yet%20built%20and%20fully%20online%2C%20and%20therefore%20estimates%20expected%20electricity%20use%20in%20the%20near%20future.%20If%20all%20permitted%20data%20centers%20go%20online%2C%20we%20estimate%2C%20they%20will%20use%20between%20149.6%20terawatt-hours%20and%20239.3%20terawatt-hours%20a%20year.%20Business%20Insider's%20low-end%20estimate%20is%20roughly%20equivalent%20to%20the%20state%20of%20Ohio's%20electricity%20needs%20in%202023%2C%20and%20on%20the%20high%20end%2C%20is%20nearly%20as%20much%20power%20as%20the%20entire%20state%20of%20Florida%20used%20that%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20estimates%20are%20conservative.%20The%20low%20end%20of%20our%20estimate%20is%20below%20the%20federal%20report's%20estimate%20for%20data%20center%20power%20use%20in%202023.%20The%20federal%20report%20estimates%20data%20center%20power%20use%20could%20reach%20the%20upper%20end%20of%20our%20estimate%20by%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20used%20the%20range%20average%20to%20identify%20the%20322%20largest%20facilities%20in%20our%20dataset%20that%2C%20according%20to%20our%20estimate%2C%20consume%2040%20megawatt-hours%20of%20electricity%20or%20more%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20methodology%20%26quot%3Boversimplifies%20complex%20data%20center%20operations%20and%20is%20based%20on%20assumptions%20that%20do%20not%20account%20for%20important%20differences%20in%20how%20companies%20build%20and%20operate%20data%20centers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20and%20Meta%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20queries%20about%20data%20center%20power%20use%20estimates%2C%20and%20QTS%20declined%20to%20comment.%20A%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%20acknowledged%20that%20its%20data%20centers%20%26quot%3Bdo%20not%20always%20run%20at%20100%25%20of%20their%20installed%20capacity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENineteen%20permits%20across%2010%20states%20%E2%80%94%20including%2012%20held%20by%20Google%20%E2%80%94%20have%20their%20generator%20capacity%20information%20fully%20or%20partially%20redacted%20under%20public%20disclosure%20exemptions%20for%20trade%20secrets.%20Business%20Insider%20was%20unable%20to%20estimate%20the%20electricity%20use%20of%20these%20facilities%2C%20so%20our%20estimate%20likely%20undercounts%20the%20true%20total.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224ee64035-8a4c-4e34-ab70-67b53ab3af47%5C%22%3ENext%2C%20we%20calculated%20data%20centers'%20likely%20public%20health%20and%20environmental%20impact%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20uses%20highly%20polluting%20fossil-fuel-fired%20sources%20for%20at%20least%2060%25%20of%20its%20electricity.%20Data%20centers%20draw%20power%20from%20a%20wide%20regional%20grid%2C%20so%20Business%20Insider%20needed%20to%20estimate%20the%20public%20health%20impact%20attributable%20to%20data%20centers'%20use%20of%20electricity%20generated%20from%20far-away%20power%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20electricity%20grid%20is%20complex%20and%20does%20not%20map%20closely%20to%20state%20boundaries.%20To%20model%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20US%20electricity%20grid%2C%20Business%20Insider%20used%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Favert%2Favert-web-edition%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnvironmental%20Protection%20Agency%20tool%20called%20AVERT%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20splits%20the%20contiguous%2048%20states%20into%2014%20independent%20electricity%20regions%20that%20approximate%20grid%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20our%20estimate%20for%20data%20center%20power%20consumption%2C%20along%20with%20US%20Energy%20Information%20Administration%20data%20and%20the%20AVERT%20tool%2C%20Business%20Insider%20calculated%20the%20likely%20share%20of%20total%20power%20use%20attributable%20to%20data%20centers%20in%20each%20of%20these%2014%20regions.%20Then%2C%20using%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcobra.epa.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEPA%20tool%20with%20the%20acronym%20COBRA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Business%20Insider%20estimated%20the%20public%20health%20cost%20engendered%20by%20that%20share%20of%20total%20electricity-generation-related%20pollution%20in%20each%20region.%20Even%20a%20careful%20calculation%20like%20this%20is%20inherently%20imperfect%2C%20but%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20industry%20transparency%20about%20such%20emissions%20it%20provides%20a%20rare%20and%20well-founded%20estimate%20of%20the%20health%20costs%20of%20the%20data%20center%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20estimated%20that%20annual%20public%20health%20costs%20from%20electricity%20generation%20for%20data%20centers%20could%20reach%20between%20%245.7%20billion%20and%20%249.2%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPower%20plants%20are%20not%20the%20only%20source%20of%20data%20center%20air%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20diesel%20backup%20generators%20installed%20at%20data%20centers%20emit%20volatile%20organic%20compounds%2C%20nitrous%20oxides%2C%20sulfur%20dioxides%2C%20and%20particulate%20matter%20%E2%80%94%20all%20regulated%20air%20pollutants%20the%20EPA%20labels%20as%20hazardous%20to%20human%20health.%20Air%20permits%20issued%20to%20these%20facilities%20set%20total%20annual%20pollutant%20emission%20limits%20that%20determine%20how%20frequently%20their%20generators%20can%20be%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20centers%20generally%20run%20their%20generators%20infrequently%20so%20emit%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20pollutants%20their%20permits%20allow.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjlarc.virginia.gov%2Flanding-2024-data-centers-in-virginia.asp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20report%20to%20the%20state%20legislature%20in%20Virginia%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20home%20to%20nearly%20a%20third%20of%20US%20data%20centers%20with%20permits%20%E2%80%94%20calculated%20that%20data%20center%20backup%20generators%20on%20average%20emit%207%25%20of%20their%20permitted%20pollution%20limits%20each%20year.%20Business%20Insider%20used%20that%20percentage%20to%20estimate%20each%20county's%20air%20pollutant%20emissions%20from%20data%20center%20backup%20generators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20then%20input%20these%20county-by-county%20totals%20into%20COBRA%2C%20which%20models%20how%20air%20pollution%20emitted%20in%20a%20county%20affects%20public%20health%20nationwide.%20The%20tool%20assigns%20a%20dollar%20figure%20to%20what%20it%20would%20cost%20to%20avoid%20negative%20health%20outcomes%20like%20premature%20deaths%2C%20asthma%20attacks%2C%20heart%20attacks%2C%20and%20missed%20school%20or%20work%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20COBRA%20tool%20estimated%20that%20air%20pollutants%20emitted%20by%20data%20centers%20across%20the%20country%20could%20trigger%20nearly%2020%2C000%20asthma%20symptom%20cases%20a%20year%20and%20create%20a%20%24385%20million%20annual%20burden%20on%20public%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerator%20pollution%20is%20more%20harmful%20to%20communities%20already%20overburdened%20by%20environmental%20pollutants.%20A%20community%20that%20already%20has%20high%20levels%20of%20air%20pollution%20will%20experience%20greater%20negative%20health%20impacts%20from%20additional%20pollutants%2C%20for%20example%2C%20than%20a%20community%20that%20isn't%20already%20saturated%20with%20harmful%20pollutants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20better%20understand%20their%20impact%20on%20these%20communities%2C%20Business%20Insider%20mapped%20all%201%2C240%20data%20center%20locations%20onto%20a%20third%20EPA%20tool%20called%20EJ%20Screen%20that%20combines%20census%20and%20pollutant%20data%20within%20a%20mile%20radius%20of%20a%20specified%20location.%20We%20found%20that%20more%20than%20230%20data%20center%20locations%20were%20in%20communities%20highly%20overburdened%20by%20environmental%20pollutants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228d26077f-eeba-4265-8286-cc5140a4cdfd%5C%22%3EFinally%2C%20we%20reported%20on%20data%20centers'%20impact%20on%20the%20economy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20requested%20and%20obtained%20the%20most%20detailed%20data-center-related%20economic%20development%20deals%20and%20annual%20tax%20incentive%20disclosures%20for%20facilities%20in%20and%20around%20Columbus%2C%20Ohio.%20Some%20of%20the%20oldest%20data%20center%20deals%20in%20the%20state%20are%20in%20Franklin%20and%20Licking%20counties%2C%20and%20companies%20are%20required%20to%20disclose%20how%20much%20they've%20saved%20from%20these%20tax%20exemption%20agreements%20each%20year%2C%20which%20made%20the%20state%20a%20useful%20case%20study%20for%20judging%20data%20centers'%20actual%20economic%20impact.%20Business%20Insider%20tallied%20these%20numbers%2C%20then%20used%20company-reported%20property%20investment%20totals%20to%20calculate%20total%20state%20and%20local%20sales%20and%20use%20tax%20savings%20(7.5%25%20for%20Franklin%20County%20and%205.75%25%20for%20Licking%20County).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20not%20include%20personal%20property%20tax%20in%20our%20calculations%2C%20as%20Ohio%20eliminated%20that%20tax.%20Because%20of%20fluctuations%20in%20the%20number%20of%20jobs%20employed%20at%20data%20centers%2C%20Business%20Insider%20also%20did%20not%20include%20state%20or%20local%20job%20creation%20tax%20credits%20in%20the%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20nevertheless%20found%20that%20these%20tax%20incentive%20packages%20given%20to%20tech%20companies%20were%20highly%20lucrative%2C%20amounting%20to%20as%20much%20as%20%242%20million%20in%20tax%20savings%20per%20full%20time%20job%20at%20a%20data%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f2fb3e4-59ce-4010-be97-181a030f0a03%5C%22%3ESeries%20credits%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReporting%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHannah%20Beckler%2C%20Dakin%20Campbell%2C%20Daniel%20Geiger%2C%20Rosemarie%20Ho%2C%20Narimes%20Parakul%2C%20Adam%20Rogers%2C%20Ellen%20Thomas%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEditing%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Jeffrey%20Cane%2C%20Rosalie%20Chan%2C%20Jason%20Dean%2C%20Esther%20Kaplan%2C%20Jake%20Swearingen%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EResearch%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Darren%20Ankrom%2C%20Schuyler%20Mitchell%2C%20Trey%20Strange%2C%20Yuheng%20Zhan%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDesign%20and%20visuals%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Dan%20DeLorenzo%2C%20Isabel%20Fernandez-Pujol%2C%20Jinpeng%20Li%2C%20Kim%20Nguyen%2C%20Randy%20Yeip%2C%20Rebecca%20Zisser%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPhotography%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Kendrick%20Brinson%2C%20John%20David-Richardson%2C%20Greg%20Kahn%2C%20Brian%20Palmer%2C%20Jesse%20Rieser%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVideo%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Robert%20Leslie%2C%20Gary%20Moon%2C%20Marco%20Secci%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECopy%20editing%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Mark%20Abadi%2C%20Kevin%20Kaplan%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-calculate-data-center-cost-environmental-impact-methodology-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750147981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6841ebc89b2a601d01b26946%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-calculate-data-center-cost-environmental-impact-methodology-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22How%20Business%20Insider%20calculated%20data%20centers'%20true%20cost%2C%20from%20their%20electricity%20and%20water%20use%20to%20their%20impact%20on%20the%20environment%20and%20public%20health.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hbeckler%40insider.com%20(Hannah%20Beckler%2CRosemarie%20Ho%2CNarimes%20Parakul%2CDakin%20Campbell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A52%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-calculate-data-center-cost-environmental-impact-methodology-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20denies%20treatment%20to%20army%20veterans%3B%20political%20views%20new%20criteria%3B%20doctors%20can%20rejec